1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,560
Hey.

2
00:00:00,560 --> 00:00:04,720
I need to reorder some flyers for my cafe's grand reopening next month.

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:06,279
Can you help me with that?

4
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:07,879
Sure. I can.

5
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,239
Let me check.

6
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,360
Oh, you're with the cozy corner. Right?

7
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:14,119
Didn't I design some flyers for you last year?

8
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:15,345
Yep. That's right.

9
00:00:15,345 --> 00:00:20,224
But we've updated our logo and added a new menu so I'll need the design to reflect that.

10
00:00:20,224 --> 00:00:21,105
Got it.

11
00:00:21,105 --> 00:00:24,365
I can have those updated and printed by the end of the week.

12
00:00:24,365 --> 00:00:27,145
By the way, would you like to see some paper options?

13
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,900
Maybe something sturdier than last time?

14
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,520
Oh, that's a great idea.

15
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:32,840
Let's go for it.

16
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:36,540
We need to come up with a new menu item for next month.

17
00:00:36,540 --> 00:00:39,389
The chefs are suggesting something light and healthy,

18
00:00:39,389 --> 00:00:42,735
like a quinoa salad with grilled vegetables.

19
00:00:42,735 --> 00:00:47,095
That sounds nice, but we already have a few healthy options on the menu.

20
00:00:47,095 --> 00:00:49,577
Maybe we should go for something more exciting,

21
00:00:49,577 --> 00:00:52,415
like a fusion dish with bold flavors.

22
00:00:52,415 --> 00:00:54,214
I thought about that too.

23
00:00:54,214 --> 00:00:56,875
How about a spicy Korean chicken wrap?

24
00:00:56,879 --> 00:01:00,960
It could be a unique twist and still keep it relatively healthy.

25
00:01:00,879 --> 00:01:02,640
I love that idea.

26
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,799
Let's pitch it to the team during the menu meeting later.

27
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,520
I'm sure they'll be on board.

28
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:09,719
Hi, Ben.

29
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:11,359
It's Lisa from City Rentals.

30
00:01:11,265 --> 00:01:15,624
Has Unit 305 been inspected for any maintenance issues yet?

31
00:01:15,624 --> 00:01:16,925
Not completely.

32
00:01:16,925 --> 00:01:20,505
The electrician was supposed to come yesterday to fix a faulty light in the living room

33
00:01:20,505 --> 00:01:22,384
but had to reschedule for tomorrow.

34
00:01:22,625 --> 00:01:24,424
We've checked the plumbing and heating,

35
00:01:24,424 --> 00:01:28,059
and both are fine, but we're still waiting on the electrical work to be completed.

36
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:29,939
That's cutting it close.

37
00:01:29,939 --> 00:01:34,240
The new tenants are moving in next Tuesday, and I really don't want any delays.

38
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:36,320
It's important we stay on schedule.

39
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,459
I understand.

40
00:01:37,459 --> 00:01:41,740
I've already spoken to the electrician, and they assured me everything will be done by Friday.

41
00:01:41,905 --> 00:01:44,544
We'll have it sorted in time for the move in.

42
00:01:46,065 --> 00:01:47,305
Good afternoon.

43
00:01:47,305 --> 00:01:50,304
This is Daniel Mitchell from GreenTech Solutions.

44
00:01:50,225 --> 00:01:53,105
I'm calling to place an order for some equipment.

45
00:01:53,025 --> 00:01:56,704
We need 50 laser printers and 200 ink cartridges, please.

46
00:01:56,730 --> 00:02:00,569
The product codes are LP10 and IC25.

47
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:02,610
Thank you for the order, mister Mitchell.

48
00:02:02,610 --> 00:02:05,589
I'm happy to let you know that we have a promotion going on right now.

49
00:02:05,589 --> 00:02:11,250
You'll get free shipping for orders over $500, and the ink cartridges are currently 10% off.

50
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:12,730
That's fantastic news.

51
00:02:12,785 --> 00:02:15,224
I'll pass it on to my purchasing department.

52
00:02:15,224 --> 00:02:16,745
They'll be happy about the savings.
